To the Honorable Governor Easley:

I was horrified to learn of the appalling, cruel, and malicious practices at the Raleigh NC animal shelter. That it has taken so long to finally cause government to take action shows an equally disturbing disregard for the innocent animals that come into the shelter by those officials to whom complaints were made time and time again.When did the word "shelter" change its definition to "NC Animal Auschwitz?"

What kind of animals have WE become to show such total indifference to the agony of animals who, through no fault of their own, wind up in an animal shelter and most likely will be put to sleep because there are just too many of them?  Would anyone let their own child slip down a drainage pipe and slowly drown? It has been documented time and again that our treatment of animals provide valuable clues to our latent behavior with respect to human society.

There is no question that being responsible for managing animal populations in area shelters is a difficult job emotionally as well as physically. Turnover at shelters is relatively high, when compared to other types of jobs. But surely we can find kinder, gentler people to treat our often callously discarded pets more humanely.

Please, when you find replacements for those responsible for these horrific treatments, administer a psychological examination, in addition to an I.Q. test and thorough background check.

Thank you for reading this to the end.

Edith Crockett

