Gentlemen:

It has come to my attention that animal cruelty in the Euthanasia Room of Wake County Animal Care & Adoption facility appears to be taking place. 

I received an email from a volunteer sent to myself (former volunteer and animal advocate) and another former volunteer.

This email appeared to have been a copy from a shelter attendant that was sent to the volunteer.  I consider this email a plea for help.

The email stated that Heidi Lewis, was seen crushing a dog's trachea to kill it.  The shelter attendant told her to stop and she continued killing the dog in this manner.  I have also "heard" and it seems to be documented, that unsedated heart stick euthanasia is or has been recently performed at this facility.

I also "heard" that the shelter director, Michael Williams, scolded the shelter attendant for "going above his head" with the complaint.  I have "heard" that the shelter attendant went to a vet on duty to report the incident.

I "heard" that Heidi Lewis has been "suspended." 

Who is doing the killing now?  Who is overseeing that Euthanasia Room?

I have "heard" and you need to open this up for the public please: that "Latoria," who I clearly remember working there, was "fired" "for improperly euthanizing cats and kittens."

I am in shock.  I am sick.  I am truly alarmed at the conditions taking place in North Carolina animal shelters.  Remember what I wrote you about Gaston County?  Today I write you about Wake County animal abuses.

I wrote you about many shelters.  I was given the shaft...the da dee da...Strange that Gaston Animal Shelter, run by President of the NC Rabies Association, Reggie Horton,  was also recently in the news for animal cruelty.  Somehow the Gaston Vet Tech College did not make the news.  Weren't they in a "fellowship" with Ralph Houser, Reggie Horton, and the NC Dept of Agriculture (turning its head the other way), in the use of Gaston shelter animals being used for "vet tech students to work on?"  Did you not receive my emails about this situation?  Did I, and many others not inform you about the cement room the vet tech used animals were forced to live in during the time they were used for "teaching models?"  Were you not asked by myself and others for records of the procedures to be pulled, and how they were being fed, watered, and offered ambient temperatures in the cement room?

Please reply.  What do you intend to do about the Euthanasia Rooms  in this state (without video cameras) monitoring euthanasia?  Who is minding the welfare of forced to die homeless animals?

Please reply.  What do you intend to do about the crushed tracheas of the dead dogs at Wake Shelter.  Are you going to send Wake Animal Control officers inside its own facility to investigate?

What will you do?  I need to know.  I am part of the taxpaying public putting peanut butter and eggs on your table.

Awaiting an immediate response.

Jane Tzilvelis
